radiographic_examinations.findings: High calcium score (432), suggestive of a high atherosclerotic plaque burden in the region of the left anterior descending artery.

Severe stenosis at the origin of the main left renal artery with a patent accessory renal artery. No stenosis of the right renal artery. Both kidneys were normal size, with symmetric excretion of contrast.

radiographic_examinations.procedure_name: Parathyroid scan with Tc-99m sestamibi and single-photon emission computed tomography/CT
radiographic_examinations.findings: Mild focal increased tracer activity on delayed images in the lower pole of the thyroid bilaterally, consistent with a parathyroid adenoma.
